	<header class="entry-header">
        		<div class="entry-meta">
			<span class="posted-on"><a href="https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/index.php/statutory-registers-to-be-maintained-by-a-company/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2020-04-08T12:46:24+00:00">April 8, 2020</time></a></span> 
			 / <a href="https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/index.php/category/companies-act-2/"><span class="post-main-category">Companies Act</span></a>		</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
        <h1 class="entry-title">Statutory Registers to be Maintained by a Company</h1>            </header>
    <div class="entry-content">
    <h3><strong>All about Statutory Registers to be maintained by the Company Under Companies Act, 2013 In India</strong></h3>
<p><strong>What are the Statutory Registers?</strong><br />
♦According to the Companies Act, Statutory Registers are the registers that contain the specific record of the company’s shareholders, directors, deposits, loan &amp; guaranty, etc. and are placed at the Registered Office of the Company.</p>
<p><strong>Why Statutory Registers are required to be maintained?</strong><br />
♦For good corporate governance and to avoid the penalties, it is always advised to maintain the Statutory Registers.<br />
♦A company shall maintain only those Statutory Registers which apply to them according to the business and transactions.</p>
<h3><span id="Statutory_Registers_required_to_be_kept_maintained_under_Section_88"><strong>Statutory Registers required to be kept &amp; maintained under Section 88:</strong></span></h3>
<h3><span id="1_Register_of_Members"><strong>1. </strong><strong>Register of Members</strong></span></h3>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-5142" src="https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Register-of-Members-1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="244" srcset="https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Register-of-Members-1.jpg 600w, https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Register-of-Members-1-480x195.jpg 480w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></p>
<h3><span id="2_Register_of_Debenture-holders"><strong>2. </strong><strong>Register of Debenture-holders</strong></span></h3>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-5141" src="https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Register-of-Debenture-holders-2.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="194" srcset="https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Register-of-Debenture-holders-2.jpg 600w, https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Register-of-Debenture-holders-2-480x155.jpg 480w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></p>
<p><strong>3. </strong><strong>Index of Members &amp; Debenture-Holders</strong><br />
♦There is no format as such for Index and rest things are all similar to the Register of Members.</p>
<p><strong>4. </strong><strong>Register &amp; Index of Beneficial Owner</strong><br />
The Company is required to maintain the Register and Index of Beneficial Owners in which entries shall be made for the beneficial owner of the shares of the Company where the share certificates are issued in the name of some other person.<br />
♦There is no format as such for Index and rest things are all similar to the Register of Members.</p>
<p><strong>5. Foreign Register of Members, Debenture Holders, Other Security Holders or Beneficial Owners Residing Outside India.</strong><br />
The Company requires to maintain the Index of Members and debenture-holders in which serial wise entries shall be made for members and debenture-holders.<br />
♦There is no format as such for Register of Foreign Members etc. and rest things are all similar to Register of Members.</p>
<h3><span id="6_Registers_of_Renewed_Duplicate_Share_Certificates"><strong>6. </strong><strong>Registers of Renewed &amp; Duplicate Share Certificates</strong></span></h3>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-5148" src="https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Registers-of-Renewed-Duplicate-Share-Certificates-3.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="285" srcset="https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Registers-of-Renewed-Duplicate-Share-Certificates-3.jpg 600w, https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Registers-of-Renewed-Duplicate-Share-Certificates-3-480x228.jpg 480w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></p>
<p><strong>7. </strong><strong>Registers of Deposits</strong><br />
♦There is no format as such for Register of Deposits and rest things are all similar to Register of Members except for the clause of Inspection and Penalty as there is nothing prescribed under Law.</p>
<p><strong>8. Registers of Employee Stock Option (ESOP)</strong><br />
The Company requires to maintain the Register of Employee Stock Option providing all the details regarding the issue, e.g. Name of the Employees to whom the shares have been allotted, Employee Code, Number of Shares allotted, Lock-in period if any, etc.<br />
♦There is no format as such for Register of ESOP and rest things are all similar to Register of Members except for the clause of Inspection and Penalty as there is nothing prescribed under Law.<strong><br />
</strong></p>
<p><span id="9_Registers_of_Sweat_Equity_Shares"><strong>9. </strong><strong>Registers of Sweat Equity Shares</strong></span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-5150" src="https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Registers-of-Sweat-Equity-Shares-4.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="245" srcset="https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Registers-of-Sweat-Equity-Shares-4.jpg 600w, https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Registers-of-Sweat-Equity-Shares-4-480x196.jpg 480w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></p>
<h3><span id="10_Registers_of_Securities_Bought_Back"><strong>10. </strong><strong>Registers of Securities Bought Back</strong></span></h3>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-5149" src="https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Registers-of-Securities-Bought-Back-5.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="313" srcset="https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Registers-of-Securities-Bought-Back-5.jpg 600w, https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Registers-of-Securities-Bought-Back-5-480x250.jpg 480w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></p>
<p><span id="11_Registers_of_Charges"><strong>11.</strong> <strong>Registers of Charges</strong></span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-5143" src="https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Registers-of-Charges-6.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="221" srcset="https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Registers-of-Charges-6.jpg 600w, https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Registers-of-Charges-6-480x177.jpg 480w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></p>
<p><strong>12. </strong><strong>Registers of Directors &amp; Key Managerial Personnel (KMP) And Their Shareholding</strong><br />
The Company is required to maintain the Register of Directors &amp; KMP and their Shareholding describing the Details of Directors such as Name, Address, PAN, etc. and their shareholding in the Company itself, its Associate Companies, Subsidiary Companies, etc.<br />
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-5145" src="https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Registers-of-Directors-Key-Managerial-Personnel-KMP-And-Their-Shareholding-7.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="356" srcset="https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Registers-of-Directors-Key-Managerial-Personnel-KMP-And-Their-Shareholding-7.jpg 600w, https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Registers-of-Directors-Key-Managerial-Personnel-KMP-And-Their-Shareholding-7-480x285.jpg 480w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></p>
<p><span id="13_Registers_of_Loan_Guarantee"><strong>13.</strong> <strong>Registers of Loan &amp; Guarantee</strong></span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-5147" src="https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Registers-of-Loan-Guarantee-8.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="329" srcset="https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Registers-of-Loan-Guarantee-8.jpg 600w, https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Registers-of-Loan-Guarantee-8-480x263.jpg 480w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></p>
<p><strong>14.</strong><strong> Registers of Investments of the Company Not Held in Its Name</strong><br />
It shall contain the particulars of the investment e.g. shares or other security which is beneficially held by the Company along with the reason for not holding it in its name. The Register shall also mention the relation under which the investment is held by the other person.<br />
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-5146" src="https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Registers-of-Investments-of-the-Company-Not-Held-in-Its-Own-Name-9.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="328" srcset="https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Registers-of-Investments-of-the-Company-Not-Held-in-Its-Own-Name-9.jpg 600w, https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Registers-of-Investments-of-the-Company-Not-Held-in-Its-Own-Name-9-480x262.jpg 480w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></p>
<p><span id="15_Registers_of_Contracts_Arrangements_in_which_Directors_Are_Interested"><strong>15.</strong> <strong>Registers of Contracts &amp; Arrangements in which Directors Are Interested</strong></span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-5144" src="https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Registers-of-Contracts-Arrangements-in-which-Directors-Are-Interested-10.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="328" srcset="https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Registers-of-Contracts-Arrangements-in-which-Directors-Are-Interested-10.jpg 600w, https://neerajbhagat.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Registers-of-Contracts-Arrangements-in-which-Directors-Are-Interested-10-480x262.jpg 480w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></p>
  </div>
